&quot;Ogre?&quot; Riverdane asked Whizbang with a raised eyebrow.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't have the slightest clue of what that woman of mine is talking about.&quot; Whizbang said with a shrug.<br>
<br>
Then Pedi's voice again, as the murmur of the crowd dwindled and faded away.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bad ogre! How many times have I told you, come at night?&quot; A long sigh from her. &quot;Here drink this up and come in before the townfolk stick you with pitchforks.&quot;<br>
<br>
A crunching sound and the tinkle of breaking glass.<br>
<br>
&quot;Drink! Not eat. You...oh never mind. You are shrunk now, come in come in....watch your head.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry Miz Pedi.&quot; her visitor said. &quot;But me so hungry. Me knew today Cookie Day, and no snacks from Miz Cami since she all cold and dead at guild house.&quot; And then the sound of cookies being devoured.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah.&quot; Whizbang said, looking at River. &quot;Not just any 'ogga'. YOUR ogga.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You have a pet ogre?&quot; Vven said in surprise.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not exactly.&quot; River began.<br>
<br>
Suddenly the loud munching stopped, and the sound of sniffing filled the air.<br>
<br>
&quot;Me nose smell something not smelled in long time.&quot; her visitor said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh?&quot; Pedi asked innocently. The sound of the basement door quietly shutting was barely audible.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ya ya.&quot; the ogre said. &quot;Me smell...&quot; Sniff. &quot;Me smell...&quot;<br>
<br>
And suddenly the sound of heavy footsteps, a lamp crashing to the ground, a chair tipping back, and the basement door swinging open with a crash.<br>
<br>
&quot;No no no!&quot; Pedi cried, &quot;You can't go down there....&quot;<br>
<br>
Footsteps banging down the stairs, and an immense figure, even shrunk down as it had to be to even enter the house, loomed in the stairway. One of the ugliest, biggest (scaled down), STUPIDEST looking ogres any of them had ever seen. Weaponry was strapped to its sides and back, making it look like a porcupine, so many sharp edges protruded from its armored body. There it stood, looking for all the world like one of the most dangerous creatures in all the land. With a huge, stupid smile on its face.<br>
<br>
&quot;OGGA!&quot; it said happily, pointing at River.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ramluk.&quot; River sighed. <br>
<br>
<br>
   ***   ***   ***<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;How....cute.&quot; Vven drawled. &quot;Is it housebroken?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;He breaks houses.&quot; River replied, watching Ramluk carefully.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ogga knew!&quot; Ramluk said proudly, beating his chest. &quot;Me knew me smelled Riverdane!&quot; Then his face fell, and the smile dropped. &quot;Miz Cami cold and no moving at guildhouse. Grelin made me go away when I try wake her up.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I know, Rammie, I know.&quot; River said softly. &quot;She's sick, and I have to find her some medicine.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Me sorry Miz Cami sick.&quot; Ramluk frowned. &quot;Miz Cami make number four best cookies. Miz Pedi number two. My momma is number one. Big momma make best cookies.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Who is between Camille and Pedi?&quot; Vven asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;Me told you! No one!&quot; Ramluk replied. Vven rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;And this is one of your guildmates?&quot; he snickered. &quot;No wonder it took your guild so long to break Hate...&quot;<br>
<br>
River shot him a murderous look. &quot;Didn't take much to drop your god, did it?&quot; Vven was silent.<br>
<br>
Whizbang was oblivious to it all. His eyes were darting back and forth between Ramluk and a rack of vintage gnomish spirits a few feet from the ogre. Back and forth. Back and forth.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ramluk....&quot; Whiz said carefully.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hmm?&quot; Ramluk said, stepping off the bottom step. He turned to Whiz, and one of his swords, arcing from the swing of his body, almost tipped the rack over.<br>
<br>
&quot;NOTHING!&quot; Whiz cried, hands up in protest. &quot;Nothing! Just....don't...move.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Silly old fool!&quot; Pedi cried in disgust. &quot;The world is about to end and you're worried about your BOOZE?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Those bottle are older than your mother LOOKS!&quot; Whizbang snapped back.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't you dare bring my mother into this, you old goa...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Enough!&quot; River exclaimed, sinking onto a stool. That stopped them midsentence. &quot;Let's figure out what to do here, ok?&quot;<br>
<br>
Whizbang cleared his throat. &quot;Of course, of course. Ok. Now, where to begin. Let's look at the prophecy first as a written piece. I already have a few theories on what this may mean. Or some of it, at least.&quot; He pointed at a few words on the page before him. &quot;Notice these words, here, here, here....a few more here. Capitilized in the middle of sentences. Like the first line, 'When Hate finds love...&quot;. What is the writer referring to?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;To me.&quot; River said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes to you, but not you as Riverdane. You as in the God of Hate. The diety. The capitilization is to name you a god, your proper title. Notice, handmaiden and enchanted dead, not capitilized. They aren't gods, no need to address them with respect or signifigance.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright, so it is my title.&quot; River said slowly, &quot;So these other capitilized words....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;...are not actually words at all, but signify other gods, yes.&quot; Whizbang finished. &quot;At least, that's what it looks like, and seems as good a place to start as any.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So this first line in the quest part,&quot; Vven interjected. &quot;'Only when Fear overcomes fear....' That's where we begin, aye? In the Plane of Fear, with Cazic-Thule, god of Fear?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;This is what I am thinking.&quot; Whizbang agreed. &quot;Though what or who Cazic may be afraid of I don't have the foggiest.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright, Vven,&quot; River said. &quot;Have you memorized this prophecy yet?&quot;<br>
<br>
Vven pointed to his head. &quot;All locked away.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you Whizbang.&quot; River said, turning to the gnome. &quot;You have started me off on my journey. Wish us luck, old man. The fate of the world depends on it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Which is exactly why I am going with you.&quot; Whizbang said, standing up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Um, Whiz, no...&quot; River said gently. &quot;This whole thing is very dangerous, and I can't take the responsibility of getting you...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;...killed?&quot; Whizbang said. His eyes narrowed. &quot;River, I have seen more years on this world than you have hairs in that mane of yours. And for all its faults, I like this world, and intend to add more years on it. If you think this wizard is going to sit idly by while a young foolhardy shadowknight and his partner Vven the Unfriendly Ghost play with the fate of it, you are sadly mistaken. I am going with you to record the events that transpire for the sake of history, and to consult and decipher the rest of the prophecy, and you will not stop me, or my name isn't Whizbang Dustyboots!&quot;<br>
<br>
One look at Whizbang's stance, and River knew his argument was lost.<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright, old man.&quot; River said. &quot;I wash my hands.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe if you did, ogga over there wouldn't have smelled you.&quot; Vven chuckled nastily.<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright, gentlemen.&quot; Pedi said, removing her apron. &quot;Let me get my armor....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You are NOT going.&quot; Whizbang declared.<br>
<br>
Pedi opened a closet and removed a red runed metal breastplate and began fastening it on with the leather straps. She did not look at Whizbang as she spoke. &quot;Whizbang, I have seen more years on this world than you have hairs missing from your head. And for all its faults, especially crotchety old wizards, I like this world, and intend...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;ALRIGHT.&quot; Whizbang exclaimed in defeat. &quot;I get the point.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Besides,&quot; she said, suddenly soft. &quot;Who's going to look after you, old man?&quot;<br>
<br>
Whizbang's frown did not give way, but his eyes smiled, as his wife went back to adjusting her armor.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where we go?&quot; Ramluk said, breaking the silence loudly, beaming at everyone in the room.<br>
<br>
&quot;We?&quot; River said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Miz Cami sick, me help.&quot; Ramluk said simply.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ramluk....&quot; River began.<br>
<br>
&quot;And Miz Pedi go. If she get sick, no more gnome cookies!&quot; Something in the ogre's tone left no argument. Riverdane sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright Ram. I can use the muscle.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; Pedi remarked, looking at them, final piece of armor in place. &quot;Don't we make a fine group.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If Innoruuk could see me now.&quot; Vven muttered. &quot;Grouped with a human, two gnomes and an OGRE.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Where we go?&quot; Ramluk repeated again.<br>
<br>
Riverdane stood up, pushing away the stool.<br>
<br>
&quot;We start in the Feeroot, Ramluk. Your birth place. And then...&quot;<br>
<br>
Ramluk smiled like a child. But River was not smiling.<br>
<br>
&quot;...to the Plane of Fear.&quot;<br>
