<br>
&quot;No need Whiz.&quot; River replied. &quot;One of my perks. I'll take us right to Ferroot itself. I don't know any safe area in Fear, so we'll go in the old fashioned way.&quot; He closed his eyes, and concentrated. A flash of light, and they were gone.<br>
<br>
They reappeared next to a large tree growing out of a hillside in the dank forest of Feeroot, home of the ogres. Crickets chirped and odd birds called out. The noise from serpents was so loud it almost sounded like one long continuous hiss. River pointed to the left of the tree. <br>
<br>
&quot;That rock face is illusory.&quot; he said. &quot;There are some spectres guarding the gateway to Fear. I'll just pull them out one at a time, and we'll dispatch them easily enough.&quot; And with that, River stepped through the rock as if it were air and disappeared from view.<br>
<br>
A short wait.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have a spectre incoming....&quot; River called from within the rock. Ramluk drew out two wicked looking swords and braced himself. They waited.<br>
<br>
&quot;Add.&quot; River called out.<br>
<br>
Vven tensed up and peered at the rock, waiting.<br>
<br>
&quot;Add.&quot; River said again, this time a little more urgently.<br>
<br>
Pedi glanced nervously at Whizbang, whose brows furled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Add.&quot; River repeated, voice going up a notch in pitch. <br>
<br>
Ramluk shifted impatiently.<br>
<br>
And out came Riverdane, with four spectres in tow, swinging their long scythes at him, skeletal faces hungry from within their hooded garb.<br>
<br>
&quot;OGGA!&quot; Ramluk roared, stepping into the mess. &quot;Help me start barshin' a spectre!&quot; His swords swung up to meet the first spectre.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sleep.&quot; Vven murmured, splaying out his fingers. One by one, the other three spectres stopped moving, mesmerized by the enchanter's spell.<br>
<br>
Ramluk and the first spectre battled, swords against scythe. River chopped at the spectre's back, Reaver cutting into the bone that made up the spectre, trying to split it open. It was tough work, the spectre being powered by some unearthly force.<br>
<br>
A swing, a chop, and the scythe cut a gash deep into Ramluk's arm. The ogre winced in pain, arm going dead, his sword dropped to the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;Healing a spectre!&quot; Pedi cried, eyes flashing blue as she chanted the heal spell.<br>
<br>
&quot;When you're done healing the enemy, &quot; Vven said dryly. &quot;You may want to fix the ogga.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oops.&quot; Pedi said redfaced. &quot;Healing Ramluk!&quot; Again the flash of blue light, and Ramluk's arm began to mend.<br>
<br>
Immediately, the Spectre turned toward Pedi and began chopping at her. She dodged in a panic to the side.<br>
<br>
Ramluk kicked hard at the spectre, to no avail. He swung and connected on the spectre's back, but still it chased Pedi around the area while she attempted to evade it. Another kick from Ramluk went unheeded.<br>
<br>
&quot;Maybe if you bothered to haste him, he may have some control.&quot; River called out to Vven. &quot;Or did you forget he was a warrior?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oops.&quot; Vven said sheepishly. &quot;Warriors blades, dance!&quot; And Vven's fingers shot white light into Ramluk. Suddenly Ramluk's swings increased speed dramatically.<br>
<br>
The spectre noticed, and turned back to Ramluk. A slice of the scythe caught Ramluk in the side, and he staggered.<br>
<br>
&quot;Healing....Ramluk!&quot; Pedi cried out again, after a disoriented pause. Blue light, and Ramluk's side began to heal.<br>
<br>
And once more the spectre was all over Pedi.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ramluk, didn't they teach you to TAUNT in warrior school?&quot; River cried in disgust.<br>
<br>
&quot;Me sorry.&quot; Ramluk said miserably, kicking at the spectre again. &quot;Me must have missed dat class.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Enough of this!&quot; Whizbang called out, leaping into the fray, hands glowing white. He glowered at the spectre. &quot;When you see your god, tell him Whizbang Dustyboots sent you!&quot;<br>
<br>
Whizbang's hands pulsed white light radiating from his body, disintigrating the spectre to dust.<br>
<br>
And pulsing out to smash the other three spectres out of their daze.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ooops?&quot; Whizbang said.<br>
<br>
&quot;How many times do I have to tell you no area spells when we have an enchanter??&quot; Pedi sighed.<br>
<br>
Ramluk kicked at a spectre, but they ignored him, all chasing the now fleeing Whizbang.<br>
<br>
&quot;Never mind, Ram, I'll tank.&quot; River said. his hands flashed darkly, as he called forth spells.<br>
<br>
&quot;Disease eat away at this foe....&quot; he called, shooting a cloud of green smoke from his fingers at the first spectre. It enveloped the spectres body, and it turned on him.<br>
<br>
River pointed at the second. &quot;Shadows, make this specter creep....&quot; And black smoke engulfed the second spectre, as it turned, as if through mud, and slowly came toward him.<br>
<br>
Then the third. &quot;Hellfire, boil the marrow of this spectre!&quot; And red smoke this time, surrounding the third and drawing it in a frenzy toward him.<br>
<br>
Good, River thought, got them off Whiz.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nice move, genius.&quot; Vven said, staring at him. &quot;You just dotted all three. Have fun.&quot; And Vven threw up his hands and sat abruptly down, watching.<br>
<br>
River opened his mouth to speak.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah,&quot; Whizbang said, running back, &quot;We know. 'Ooops'.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Ramluk, tank mez the left one.&quot; River said. &quot;I have the middle. Whiz, root and shoot the third.&quot;<br>
<br>
Whizbang muttered something in gnomish. Roots suddenly flailed up from the earth, twisting themselves into the skeletal form of the spectre to the right. It held it fast to the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know, I know,&quot; Whizbang said to the glowering trapped spectre. &quot;You hate gnomes.&quot; <br>
<br>
BOOM.<br>
<br>
Whizbang blew smoke from his fingertips, having unleashed a firey bolt that all but destroyed the spectre.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile Ramluk had one engaged and was methodically beating it down into the ground. The disease cloud from River was weakening its bone structure, and Ramluk's slices and pounding on it shattered it into little pieces.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile, River was still locked in battle with the last spectre. It drew back its scythe high to chop at River's head. That's when River saw his opening.<br>
<br>
His hand shot out into the robe of the spectre, hand clamping around the bone that made the spectre's neck. His hand glowed with blacklight.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bye bye.&quot; River said.<br>
<br>
--PULSE--<br>
<br>
With a muffled pop, Riverdane's harmtouch blew the spectre's head off its body. The arms holding the scythe went limp as the body collapsed lifelessly to the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; Vven said, standing up. &quot;Don't we just suck.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Warming up.&quot; River said defensively. &quot;Shall we enter Fear?&quot;<br>
<br>
And with that he trudged back into the illusory slab of rock. They warily followed him, Whizbang in the back.<br>
<br>
&quot;If we're the only hope the world has for survival,&quot; he muttered to Pedi. &quot;I feel sorry for the world.&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
   ***   ***   ***<br>
<br>
<br>
A gateway of Fire. Portal to the Plane of Fear.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know what's on the other side.&quot; Riverdane said to his four companions. &quot;And I don't know if it will acknowledge me as a god. Nor if it did if it would matter.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So basically...&quot; Whizbang began.<br>
<br>
&quot;....I don't know anything. Right.&quot; River finished. &quot;Shall we?&quot;<br>
<br>
With a nod from Whiz, all five stepped through the fire. It crackled and hissed as they passed through, but none were burned.<br>
<br>
Into Fear. A huge hilly area, with twisted, insane architecture and monoliths, with a large building in the center surrounded by a flaming moat. Fear, home of Cazic Thule, where when the skies wept, they cried blood rather than rain.<br>
<br>
&quot;Portal seems clear.&quot; Vven said, eyes darting around.<br>
<br>
River looked off to his left. &quot;So does the way to the west wall.&quot; River commented.<br>
<br>
&quot;Too clear.&quot; Vven added.<br>
<br>
&quot;Someone's here.&quot; Whizbang said. &quot;This is too empty.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;AKETHADAR!&quot; A loud booming voice called, the sound echoing through the grassy hills.<br>
<br>
And then the sound of chuckling to the west, on the other side of a hillock.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ake got owned again.&quot; said a mild voice, with an odd ogre accent. &quot;Who wants to get get him?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not me, I have to med.&quot; said a second person, clearly human. &quot;Tremas, you get him this time.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Wizzie gets no love.&quot; the third voice, presumably Tremas. It had the rich bass tones of a Eruidite. &quot;Where do you think I get this mana from, Aamedor, my good looks?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I thought you stored it all in that huge forehead of yours.&quot; the ogre voice cut in.<br>
<br>
&quot;Kiss my ass, Pron.&quot; Tremas said back. &quot;Alright, I'll get Ake this time. But give me a little downtime too, not like we doing this with a chanter.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Lovely,&quot; Riverdane said. &quot;Promethian Order is here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I take it this isn't a good thing?&quot; Pedi said, looking at the expression on River's face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; River hedged. &quot;I'm fine with most of them. Aamedor is old Razor's Edge. Let's just say Akethadar and I have a little history. Let's go say hello.&quot; And they followed him up and over the hill.<br>
<br>
Promethian Order. One of the oldest and affluent military guilds of Norrath. Acceptance into the ranks of Promethian Order was akin to an adventurer coming of age. Its members had seen many things other guilds only dream of doing. And there were two of the members, sitting among a pile of corpses of the denizens of Fear. Dead scarelings, phoboplasms, nightmares, turmoil toads littered the camp site. And in the middle, Pron, a huge ogre warlord in full battle gear, and Aamedor, one of Promethian Order's high priests and former member of River's guild. Tremas was nowhere to be seen.<br>
<br>
Aamedor saw them first. &quot;Hey, River.&quot; he said with a smile. &quot;And Whiz, Pedi. What brings you here? Alliance coming up?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hi, Aam.&quot; River said, clasping wrists with the cleric. Whizbang nodded his hello. &quot;Actually, here for Cazic Thule.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hehh.&quot; Pron chuckled. &quot;Promethian is coming here in a little while. The only thing left will be his corpse, I'm afraid.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ramluk was staring with his mouth open at Pron's array of weaponry and gear. &quot;Ogga!&quot; he said in amazement.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes,&quot; Pron said in perfect common. &quot;I am of ogre descent.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You talk funny.&quot; Ramluk said, a confused look on his stupid face.<br>
<br>
&quot;I was educated in the finest schools in the Plane of Knowledge, if that's what you refer to as 'funny'.&quot; Pron remarked loftily. Then his eyes narrowed as he looked at Ramluk's armor. &quot;My gods, man, where did you get your armor? Did you mother make it for you?&quot;<br>
<br>
Ramluk looked at his feet with embarrassment, an emotion ill-suited to one his size. &quot;Ya, Big Momma make me armors.&quot;<br>
<br>
And then in came Tremas, dragging the dead body of a human. Tremas was dressed in an ornately decorate robe of many hues, his hood partially covering the freakishly high forehead that was the staple look of Erudite men. The corpse he carried in was dressed in the light garb of a professional monk.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey, Riv, what's shakin'?&quot; Tremas asked. Tremas, publicity officer of Promethian, had dealt with River often in the past when the two guilds had bumped heads. &quot;And Whizbang....wiz power....!&quot; And Tremas made a symbol with his hand that Whiz smiled and emulated. Pedi sighed. Vven just watched quietly, looking around, waiting for anything to appear and leap at them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ake bit it again, Fright is up and deathtouching.&quot; Tremas said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Must be...unpleasant.&quot; Vven commented.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hah,&quot; Tremas said. &quot;I swear he likes it. I think he's a rez junkie. All pullers must be.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Rezzing Akethadar....&quot; Aamedor intoned, hands and eyes glowing with blue light. The light shot out from Aamedor's hands to infuse the corpse of Akethadar. And Akethadar's eyes snapped open.<br>
<br>
&quot;YOU HAVE FIVE MINUTES TO MED BEFORE I BEGIN PULLING AGAIN.&quot; Akethadar said loudly, pulling himself to his feet.<br>
<br>
Ramluk winced at the noise. &quot;No need to shout...&quot; Pedi said.<br>
<br>
Akethadar favored her with a dour look, and then spotted Riverdane.<br>
<br>
&quot;River.&quot; he said, striding up to him. &quot;So, progressing from stealing camps in The Grey to stealing them in Fear, huh?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I told you last time, Ake,&quot; River sighed. &quot;I was new to the area and didn't...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I told you then, and I am telling you now.&quot; Akethadar cut him off. &quot;You will not stand in the way or interfere with Promethian Order or we will march across you like a rug. Stay out of our way and your lives can go on in the mundane way they always do. Get in my way and we will sweep you aside like the dust you are.&quot;<br>
<br>
River held his temper. &quot;We're not here to interfere with your raid, Ake. I just need to speak with Cazic-Thule.&quot;<br>
<br>
Akethadar looked at him incredulously. And then laughed. Loudly. His three companions joined in.<br>
<br>
&quot;You five are going to walk into the home of Cazic?&quot; he asked. &quot;YOU five? We just cleared most of fear with four people and WE wouldn't just walk in there.&quot; He chuckled nastily. &quot;Remember to consent and after we destroy Cazic, I'll have Aamedor here resurrect your dead bodies.&quot; And then, not glancing again at them, he turned to his three companions.<br>
<br>
&quot;I AM GOING TO PULL. BE READY FOR SINGLES APPROACHING FROM THE SOUTH.&quot; And he disappeared over the hill.<br>
<br>
